The paper deals with the computational complexity of probabilistic planning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the evaluation and existence of plans, which involves optimization and decision-making, making it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions complexity classes such as PL, P, NP, co-NP, PP, and PSPACE, indicating that it is related to computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and programming languages (cs.PL).
